---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/sections/Navbar.astro';
import MenuDrawer from '../../components/sections/MenuDrawer.astro';
import CityPickerDialog from '../../components/sections/CityPickerDialog.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/sections/Footer.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/atoms/Breadcrumb.astro';

const url = Astro.url.toString();
const schemaLD = [
  {
    '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
    itemListElement: [
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://japanauto.ca/' },
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'About', item: url },
    ],
  },
  {
    '@type': 'WebPage',
    '@id': `${url}#page`,
    name: 'About japanauto.ca',
    description: 'What japanauto.ca is, who runs it, and how it makes money.',
    url,
    inLanguage: 'en-CA',
    publisher: { '@id': 'https://japanauto.ca/#organization' },
  },
];
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About japanauto.ca"
  description="What japanauto.ca is, who runs it, and how it makes money — an independent Calgary-based marketplace for used Japanese cars and salvage-yard parts."
  canonical={url}
  schemaLD={schemaLD}
>
  <Navbar slot="navbar" />
  <MenuDrawer slot="menu-drawer" />
  <CityPickerDialog slot="city-picker" />
  <Footer slot="footer" />

  <Breadcrumb
    items={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'About' },
    ]}
  />

  <article class="section" style="padding-top:8px;max-width:720px">
    <h1 class="t-display-l" style="font-size:30px;line-height:38px;margin-bottom:16px">About japanauto.ca</h1>

    <p class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin-bottom:14px">
      japanauto.ca is a focused Canadian marketplace for used Japanese vehicles and salvage-yard donor
      parts. We bring together listings from licensed dealers and salvage yards across six metros —
      Toronto, Montreal, Vancouver, Calgary, Edmonton and Ottawa — and put them in one place that is
      easy to search. We are an aggregator, not the seller. Every car and every part belongs to the
      dealer or yard named on the listing, and the sale happens directly between you and them.
    </p>

    <h2 class="t-h-l" style="font-size:20px;line-height:28px;margin:24px 0 10px">Why Japanese-only</h2>
    <p class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin-bottom:14px">
      A narrow marketplace is a more useful one. By covering only Japanese makes and the yards that
      part them out, we can organize inventory the way an owner actually thinks — by model, generation,
      engine code and the specific donor part you need. A generalist listings site cannot do that well
      across every brand. It also lets us build reference material — model histories, common-fault
      notes, parts-fitment context — that stays accurate because the scope is contained. If you are
      shopping a Japanese car or hunting a part for one, this site is built around your search rather
      than trying to serve everyone at once.
    </p>

    <h2 class="t-h-l" style="font-size:20px;line-height:28px;margin:24px 0 10px">How we help buyers</h2>
    <p class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin-bottom:14px">
      Listings carry the vehicle&#39;s VIN so you can run your own history check before you contact a
      seller, and we validate VIN format on the way in rather than accepting whatever is typed. Where
      it matters, we explain the rules that govern a purchase — the difference between buying from an
      AMVIC-licensed dealer in Alberta or an OMVIC-licensed dealer in Ontario versus a private seller,
      and what a salvage or rebuilt title means for a car or a part. We show honest empty states: if a
      city or model has no matching inventory today, the page says so plainly. We do not pad results
      with fake or expired listings to look busier than we are.
    </p>

    <h2 class="t-h-l" style="font-size:20px;line-height:28px;margin:24px 0 10px">How we make money</h2>
    <p class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin-bottom:14px">
      Buyers pay nothing to search or contact a seller. Our revenue comes from dealers and salvage
      yards who list with us. There is a Free tier and a paid <strong style="color:var(--color-ink-strong);font-weight:600">Pro</strong>
      subscription with higher listing limits and more tools; every new seller account starts with a
      30-day Pro trial, no card required. Separately, official-brand dealers can buy a featured
      new-vehicle placement on their brand&#39;s model pages in a city — one dealer per brand per city.
      Those placements are always disclosed as sponsored and kept out of the ranked listing results.
      See <a href="/dealers/pricing/" style="color:var(--color-ink-strong);text-decoration:underline">dealer pricing</a>
      for the full breakdown.
    </p>

    <h2 class="t-h-l" style="font-size:20px;line-height:28px;margin:24px 0 10px">Editorial integrity</h2>
    <p class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin-bottom:14px">
      Our guides and explainers are kept separate from what advertisers pay for. Manufacturers and
      dealers cannot buy editorial coverage or a better review, and sponsored placements never appear
      inside editorial content without a clear label. How we research, fact-check and update that
      content is documented in our
      <a href="/editorial-policy/" style="color:var(--color-ink-strong);text-decoration:underline">editorial policy</a>,
      and the people who write and review it are named on the
      <a href="/editorial-team/" style="color:var(--color-ink-strong);text-decoration:underline">editorial team page</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="t-h-l" style="font-size:20px;line-height:28px;margin:24px 0 10px">Who runs it</h2>
    <p class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin-bottom:14px">
      japanauto.ca is built and operated by an independent Canadian IT company based in Calgary,
      Alberta. We are not owned by a manufacturer, a dealer group or a listings conglomerate. We do
      plan to add an AMVIC-licensed dealership arm in the future, but it will be run as a separate
      business and kept at arm&#39;s length from the marketplace. The reason is simple: a marketplace
      that also sells cars has an incentive to favour its own inventory, and we would rather remove
      that temptation by structure than ask you to trust that we resist it. If and when the dealership
      lists on the site, it will appear under a neutral brand and follow exactly the same rules as any
      other seller.
    </p>

    <h2 class="t-h-l" style="font-size:20px;line-height:28px;margin:24px 0 10px">Where to go next</h2>
    <p class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin-bottom:14px">
      Browse <a href="/used-cars/" style="color:var(--color-ink-strong);text-decoration:underline">used cars</a>,
      search <a href="/parts/" style="color:var(--color-ink-strong);text-decoration:underline">salvage-yard parts</a>,
      or if you sell vehicles or part them out, see
      <a href="/dealers/pricing/" style="color:var(--color-ink-strong);text-decoration:underline">dealer pricing</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="t-h-l" style="font-size:20px;line-height:28px;margin:24px 0 10px">Contact</h2>
    <p class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin-bottom:14px">
      Questions, feedback or corrections — email
      <a href="mailto:support@japanauto.ca" style="color:var(--color-ink-strong);text-decoration:underline">support@japanauto.ca</a>
      or call <a href="tel:+18335272622" style="color:var(--color-ink-strong);text-decoration:underline">1-833-527-2622</a>.
      For a specific car or part, contact the seller directly through the listing page.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
